A couple of days ago I quickly had to create a result type that would transform a Rome (https://rome.dev.java.net/) SyndFeed to several news feeds. The framework makes this very, very easy. I just needed to implement the ResultType interface and annotate it with @ResultType. Here's a simple example:

```java
@ResultType
public class SyndFeedResultType implements ResultType {
    public Object getResultType() {
        return SyndFeed.class;
    }
}
```

Then, in my action class, I just needed to declare a field of type SyndFeed and the framework took care of the rest:

```java
public class NewsAction extends Action {
    private SyndFeed feed;

    // ...
}
```

The framework automatically transformed the SyndFeed object to the appropriate news feeds based on the accept header of the request. It was really that simple!

